                            {
                                "titre": "Use cement or concrete mix, either one will work. While concrete is stronger than just cement, on a small scale project like this the lack of aggregates won't matter as much.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "In fact cement works better than concrete, since there are no gravel pieces and the whole mixture fills small cavities perfectly, so the end result is flawless.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Cement doesn't usually stick to PLA too much, so mould release is not strictly necessary, but I like to spray some WD-40 on the insde of the mould just in case.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Mix a batch or cement- white, pale gray or dark gray (whatever is available in your country), add pigments if you want to and pour into the mould.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Bang the whole mould onto the countertop to release any air bubbles and to spread the mixture evenly. Level the top and leave to set.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
